WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.600
I will give thanks to the Lord with my whole heart.

2
00:00:02.600 --> 00:00:04.960
I'll recount all of your wonderful deeds.

3
00:00:04.960 --> 00:00:06.840
I will be glad and exulting you.

4
00:00:06.840 --> 00:00:09.920
I will sing praise to your name, O Most High.

5
00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:11.220
When my enemies turn back,

6
00:00:11.220 --> 00:00:13.800
they stumble and perish before your presence.

7
00:00:13.800 --> 00:00:16.000
For you have maintained my just cause.

8
00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:19.280
You have sat on the throne, giving righteous judgment.

9
00:00:19.280 --> 00:00:20.960
You have rebuked the nations.

10
00:00:20.960 --> 00:00:22.600
You have made the wicked perish.

11
00:00:22.600 --> 00:00:25.400
You have blotted out their name forever and ever.

12
00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:30.400
The enemy came to an end in everlasting ruins.

13
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:32.160
Their cities he rooted out.

14
00:00:32.160 --> 00:00:34.480
The very memory of them has perished.

15
00:00:34.480 --> 00:00:36.760
But the Lord sits and thrown forever.

16
00:00:36.760 --> 00:00:39.360
He has established his throne for justice.

17
00:00:39.360 --> 00:00:41.720
And he judges the world with righteousness.

18
00:00:41.720 --> 00:00:44.980
He judges the peoples with uprightness.

19
00:00:44.980 --> 00:00:47.400
The Lord is a stronghold for the oppressed,

20
00:00:47.400 --> 00:00:49.380
a stronghold in times of trouble.

21
00:00:51.080 --> 00:00:54.200
And those who know your name put their trust in you.

22
00:00:54.200 --> 00:00:57.720
For you, O Lord, have not forsaken those who seek you.

23
00:00:57.720 --> 00:01:01.440
Sing praises to the Lord who sits and thrown in Zion.

24
00:01:01.440 --> 00:01:03.480
Tell among the peoples his deeds.

25
00:01:03.480 --> 00:01:06.520
For he who avenges blood is mindful of them.

26
00:01:06.520 --> 00:01:09.080
He does not forget the cry of the afflicted.

27
00:01:09.080 --> 00:01:10.760
Be gracious to me, O Lord,

28
00:01:10.760 --> 00:01:13.320
see my affliction from those who hate me.

29
00:01:13.320 --> 00:01:15.800
O you who lift me up from the gates of death,

30
00:01:15.800 --> 00:01:17.760
that I may recount all your praises,

31
00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:20.000
that in the gates of the daughter of Zion,

32
00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:22.760
I may rejoice in your salvation.

33
00:01:22.760 --> 00:01:25.680
The nations have sunk in the pit that they have made,

34
00:01:25.680 --> 00:01:29.640
and the net that they hid their own foot has been caught.

35
00:01:29.640 --> 00:01:31.840
The Lord has made himself known.

36
00:01:31.840 --> 00:01:34.840
He has executed judgment, the wicked are snared

37
00:01:34.840 --> 00:01:36.840
in the work of their own hands.

38
00:01:36.840 --> 00:01:38.720
The wicked shall return to shield,

39
00:01:38.720 --> 00:01:41.000
and the nations that forget God.

40
00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:43.360
For the needy shall not always be forgotten,

41
00:01:43.360 --> 00:01:45.960
and the hope of the poor shall not perish forever.

42
00:01:45.960 --> 00:01:49.400
Arise, O Lord, let not man prevail,

43
00:01:49.400 --> 00:01:51.800
let the nations be judged before you.

44
00:01:51.800 --> 00:01:53.440
Put them in fear, O Lord,

45
00:01:53.440 --> 00:01:56.720
let the nations know that they are but men.

46
00:01:56.720 --> 00:01:58.080
This is the word of the Lord.

47
00:02:01.760 --> 00:02:05.080
Let's pray together once again as we come to Psalm nine.

48
00:02:07.720 --> 00:02:11.440
Lord, as I'm stood here, reminded of what we looked at

49
00:02:11.440 --> 00:02:13.400
last week in Psalm eight,

50
00:02:14.480 --> 00:02:16.920
that it is out of the mouths of babies and infants

51
00:02:16.920 --> 00:02:19.240
that you have established strength,

52
00:02:19.280 --> 00:02:23.240
because of your foes, to still the enemy and the Avenger.

53
00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:28.600
Lord, your strength is made perfect in weakness.

54
00:02:28.600 --> 00:02:33.280
And Lord, I pray that in our weakness this morning,

55
00:02:34.160 --> 00:02:39.160
as frail people, Lord, that you would make your strength known.

56
00:02:40.120 --> 00:02:44.680
Lord, I pray that you would powerfully speak to us

57
00:02:44.680 --> 00:02:48.040
by your spirit as we open your word together.

58
00:02:48.040 --> 00:02:50.680
Would you show us more of Jesus

59
00:02:50.680 --> 00:02:52.960
and what it means to trust in Him?

60
00:02:52.960 --> 00:02:54.840
With His name we pray, amen.

61
00:02:56.760 --> 00:02:57.600
Amen.

62
00:02:57.600 --> 00:03:00.360
Well, I'm not much of a sports guy at all.

63
00:03:00.360 --> 00:03:02.360
If you've gotten to know me, you'll know that that's the case.

64
00:03:02.360 --> 00:03:04.320
I kind of get lost as you talk about

65
00:03:04.320 --> 00:03:06.600
whatever team you're interested in or whatever.

66
00:03:06.600 --> 00:03:08.600
But there have been times when I couldn't help

67
00:03:08.600 --> 00:03:11.040
but get kind of swept up in celebrations

68
00:03:11.040 --> 00:03:12.200
that are happening.

69
00:03:12.200 --> 00:03:14.200
Specifically, I think of when we were living

70
00:03:14.200 --> 00:03:16.360
in Leicester, England, we moved there.

71
00:03:16.480 --> 00:03:18.880
The year that Leicester won the premiership.

72
00:03:18.880 --> 00:03:21.920
And it was like, I mean, nobody expected that to happen.

73
00:03:21.920 --> 00:03:25.240
You're talking like 5,000 to one odds.

74
00:03:25.240 --> 00:03:27.640
And I talk about excitement.

75
00:03:27.640 --> 00:03:29.560
Like I was all of a sudden a Leicester city fan,

76
00:03:29.560 --> 00:03:30.720
just like the rest of the city.

77
00:03:30.720 --> 00:03:34.240
Because they brought back the trophy on this double-decker bus

78
00:03:34.240 --> 00:03:37.000
and there were far more people outside their homes

79
00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:38.760
in the city than inside their homes.

80
00:03:38.760 --> 00:03:41.680
Hundreds of thousands, that's no exaggeration.

81
00:03:41.680 --> 00:03:43.840
We're aligning the streets and like seeing that trophy

82
00:03:43.840 --> 00:03:45.360
was brought in.

83
00:03:45.760 --> 00:03:48.200
And then everybody then went to this local park,

84
00:03:48.200 --> 00:03:50.880
Victoria Park, we all cheered on the team

85
00:03:50.880 --> 00:03:52.040
as they presented their trophy,

86
00:03:52.040 --> 00:03:55.960
having won this huge event.

87
00:03:55.960 --> 00:03:59.000
And victory celebrations have a long history.

88
00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:01.400
It goes way back before the sports

89
00:04:01.400 --> 00:04:03.040
that we think of today.

90
00:04:03.040 --> 00:04:04.680
I mean, even in scripture, when you look at it,

91
00:04:04.680 --> 00:04:06.640
you see a number of victory celebrations

92
00:04:06.640 --> 00:04:07.480
that are happening.

93
00:04:07.480 --> 00:04:10.280
So you have like the crossing of the Red Sea, right?

94
00:04:10.280 --> 00:04:13.600
So Pharaoh and his armies are defeated.

95
00:04:13.640 --> 00:04:15.520
Moses and God's people are on the other side.

96
00:04:15.520 --> 00:04:17.200
You immediately in scripture have them

97
00:04:17.200 --> 00:04:19.320
this song that's being sung.

98
00:04:19.320 --> 00:04:21.200
Praise in God for this victory.

99
00:04:22.800 --> 00:04:25.280
You got this famous case of David and Goliath

100
00:04:25.280 --> 00:04:27.240
and the Philistines being defeated.

101
00:04:27.240 --> 00:04:30.320
And as the armies come back in,

102
00:04:30.320 --> 00:04:31.560
women come out in the streets

103
00:04:31.560 --> 00:04:33.440
and they're singing a song of victory.

104
00:04:33.440 --> 00:04:37.680
So they're singing, David has killed his thousands.

105
00:04:37.680 --> 00:04:40.520
Or no, Saul has killed his thousands, that was it.

106
00:04:40.520 --> 00:04:42.560
But David is tens of thousands, right?

107
00:04:42.600 --> 00:04:45.720
So victory followed by celebration and praise.

108
00:04:46.600 --> 00:04:47.880
Then you get to the end of the Bible.

109
00:04:47.880 --> 00:04:49.040
So revelation.

110
00:04:49.040 --> 00:04:52.840
The city of Babylon is as fallen in Revelation 18

111
00:04:52.840 --> 00:04:54.840
and God's kingdom is established.

112
00:04:54.840 --> 00:04:58.920
And then Revelation 19, you then have praise

113
00:04:58.920 --> 00:05:00.800
being given to God because that has happened.

114
00:05:00.800 --> 00:05:03.200
So you see that pattern right the way through.

115
00:05:03.200 --> 00:05:05.640
And the Psalms are full of praise

116
00:05:05.640 --> 00:05:09.440
and that includes these celebrations of victory as well,

117
00:05:09.440 --> 00:05:12.200
victory over God's enemies.

118
00:05:12.200 --> 00:05:15.840
In fact, the theme of praise is just gonna be repetitive

119
00:05:15.840 --> 00:05:16.680
over and over.

120
00:05:16.680 --> 00:05:18.320
So the book of Psalms as we said already

121
00:05:18.320 --> 00:05:20.200
is broken up into five different books.

122
00:05:20.200 --> 00:05:22.280
And at the end of each one of those books,

123
00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:24.520
no matter how hard things have been,

124
00:05:24.520 --> 00:05:27.600
they all end in this kind of crescendo of praise to God.

125
00:05:27.600 --> 00:05:31.400
So prayer is always leading to praise.

126
00:05:31.400 --> 00:05:34.080
Well this Psalm is one of those Psalms of praise,

127
00:05:34.080 --> 00:05:39.080
particularly after a victory that has been won.

128
00:05:39.080 --> 00:05:40.980
But I wanna draw your attention to something specific

129
00:05:40.980 --> 00:05:42.660
that is different about this

130
00:05:42.660 --> 00:05:46.220
when it comes to a celebration of victory.

131
00:05:46.220 --> 00:05:48.940
Because the first 12 verses praise God

132
00:05:48.940 --> 00:05:52.940
as a victorious king who has triumphed over his enemies.

133
00:05:52.940 --> 00:05:56.160
But then beginning in verse 13, what do we see?

134
00:05:56.160 --> 00:06:01.160
You see that David is still presently under attack.

135
00:06:01.620 --> 00:06:04.540
So in other words, he is praising God

136
00:06:04.540 --> 00:06:06.820
in the middle of the battle,

137
00:06:06.820 --> 00:06:08.260
knowing that the outcome,

138
00:06:08.260 --> 00:06:11.700
the kind of victorious outcome is secure.

139
00:06:11.700 --> 00:06:15.300
So yes, it's a celebration of the victory of God,

140
00:06:15.300 --> 00:06:18.540
but it's a victory that is yet to see fully happen.

141
00:06:19.820 --> 00:06:21.460
So you have that pattern all the way through

142
00:06:21.460 --> 00:06:23.700
of victory celebration,

143
00:06:23.700 --> 00:06:28.060
but here it's celebration because of future victory.

144
00:06:28.060 --> 00:06:30.300
And David invites us into this praise

145
00:06:30.300 --> 00:06:31.380
that he is singing here.

146
00:06:31.380 --> 00:06:33.180
So verse 11, for example,

147
00:06:33.180 --> 00:06:35.300
he says, sing praises to the Lord

148
00:06:35.300 --> 00:06:37.940
who sits enthroned in Zion.

149
00:06:37.940 --> 00:06:41.780
Tell among the people his deeds

150
00:06:41.780 --> 00:06:44.220
so we can celebrate God's victory

151
00:06:44.220 --> 00:06:47.220
while the battle is still raging.

152
00:06:48.180 --> 00:06:50.300
This is calling us to look to God

153
00:06:50.300 --> 00:06:52.140
in the face of overwhelming odds

154
00:06:52.140 --> 00:06:54.980
and to praise him anyway.

155
00:06:54.980 --> 00:06:59.300
In other words, when everything seems to be going wrong,

156
00:06:59.300 --> 00:07:01.820
the piano's not working and whatever,

157
00:07:01.820 --> 00:07:03.660
we can praise God anyway.

158
00:07:03.660 --> 00:07:05.860
You would think that was a planned illustration.

159
00:07:06.860 --> 00:07:09.780
So I've titled this sermon.

160
00:07:09.780 --> 00:07:11.300
I don't always make a lot of titles,

161
00:07:11.300 --> 00:07:12.820
but this I thought, well,

162
00:07:12.820 --> 00:07:16.100
the theme really here is defiant praise.

163
00:07:16.100 --> 00:07:18.340
It's like circumstances seem to be saying one thing,

164
00:07:18.340 --> 00:07:21.380
but I'm gonna praise God anyway.

165
00:07:21.380 --> 00:07:24.460
Now we're not gonna look at every single phrase

166
00:07:24.460 --> 00:07:26.300
in Psalm nine or every single word.

167
00:07:26.300 --> 00:07:27.620
There's a lot of similar themes

168
00:07:27.620 --> 00:07:30.500
that we've already seen in Psalms up to this point,

169
00:07:30.500 --> 00:07:32.220
but we're gonna see the gist,

170
00:07:32.220 --> 00:07:34.860
the kind of main emphasis of the Psalm

171
00:07:35.060 --> 00:07:36.980
and we're gonna particularly focus on this kind of aspect

172
00:07:36.980 --> 00:07:38.540
of defiant praise.

173
00:07:38.540 --> 00:07:41.260
So we're gonna look at kind of three things.

174
00:07:41.260 --> 00:07:42.660
I mean, one we've already looked at

175
00:07:42.660 --> 00:07:44.020
and that's when we praise, right?

176
00:07:44.020 --> 00:07:45.460
That kind of defiant praise.

177
00:07:45.460 --> 00:07:46.900
So we're not gonna spend time with that,

178
00:07:46.900 --> 00:07:48.900
but the other two things I want us to see then,

179
00:07:48.900 --> 00:07:50.100
so if we're gonna praise God

180
00:07:50.100 --> 00:07:52.060
within this kind of defiant way,

181
00:07:52.060 --> 00:07:54.660
we're gonna see how we are to praise him

182
00:07:54.660 --> 00:07:57.860
and then also why we are going to praise him, all right?

183
00:07:57.860 --> 00:08:00.900
So how and why is essentially what we're gonna be looking at.

184
00:08:00.900 --> 00:08:01.940
So how we praise God?

185
00:08:01.940 --> 00:08:03.860
Well, the first two verses,

186
00:08:03.860 --> 00:08:06.220
David is repeating these I will statements.

187
00:08:06.220 --> 00:08:07.820
I will, I will.

188
00:08:07.820 --> 00:08:09.540
He's resolved to praise,

189
00:08:09.540 --> 00:08:11.140
but not only to praise,

190
00:08:11.140 --> 00:08:14.020
he's resolved to praise in the way he describes here.

191
00:08:14.020 --> 00:08:15.660
So let's read it again.

192
00:08:15.660 --> 00:08:19.620
He says, I will give thanks to the Lord with my whole heart.

193
00:08:19.620 --> 00:08:23.500
I will recount all of your wonderful deeds.

194
00:08:23.500 --> 00:08:26.940
I will be glad and exult in you.

195
00:08:26.940 --> 00:08:28.980
I will sing praise to your name,

196
00:08:28.980 --> 00:08:31.780
oh most high God.

197
00:08:33.300 --> 00:08:35.700
So he's resolved that he's gonna praise God

198
00:08:35.700 --> 00:08:37.500
in a particular way.

199
00:08:37.500 --> 00:08:39.580
Now music styles have changed over the years.

200
00:08:39.580 --> 00:08:41.180
Like I mostly grew up in churches

201
00:08:41.180 --> 00:08:42.820
that kind of like chop the air,

202
00:08:42.820 --> 00:08:44.020
you know with the old hymns,

203
00:08:44.020 --> 00:08:45.360
you're standing there holding your hymn book

204
00:08:45.360 --> 00:08:46.700
and that kind of thing.

205
00:08:46.700 --> 00:08:49.420
And then we tried to go to that a modern church

206
00:08:49.420 --> 00:08:51.020
for a little while that had a praise team

207
00:08:51.020 --> 00:08:52.740
and we were singing all these modern songs

208
00:08:52.740 --> 00:08:54.580
like Lord, I lift your name on high

209
00:08:54.580 --> 00:08:56.260
and shine, Jesus shine.

210
00:08:56.580 --> 00:08:58.380
It's interesting though,

211
00:08:58.380 --> 00:08:59.820
when you look at styles of praise,

212
00:08:59.820 --> 00:09:02.500
like how quick something that's kind of modern

213
00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:05.220
can feel like quaint to everybody else,

214
00:09:05.220 --> 00:09:06.500
even though it feels modern to you

215
00:09:06.500 --> 00:09:08.860
because styles change over generations

216
00:09:08.860 --> 00:09:10.340
and in different cultures,

217
00:09:10.340 --> 00:09:13.220
but the substance of praise

218
00:09:13.220 --> 00:09:16.060
should be the same throughout the generations

219
00:09:16.060 --> 00:09:16.900
across cultures.

220
00:09:16.900 --> 00:09:18.660
So the very substance of David's praise

221
00:09:18.660 --> 00:09:22.180
should be the substance of our praise.

222
00:09:22.180 --> 00:09:23.160
And if I had to summarize

223
00:09:23.160 --> 00:09:26.120
what the substance of David's praise

224
00:09:27.320 --> 00:09:29.000
or what the substance of David's praise

225
00:09:29.000 --> 00:09:29.960
is characterized by,

226
00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:31.160
like what would the word be?

227
00:09:31.160 --> 00:09:34.280
I'd have to say integrity.

228
00:09:34.280 --> 00:09:36.800
David praises God with integrity.

229
00:09:36.800 --> 00:09:39.520
In other words, there is an integration

230
00:09:39.520 --> 00:09:42.640
of his internal devotion

231
00:09:42.640 --> 00:09:46.160
and these external expressions of praise.

232
00:09:46.160 --> 00:09:48.960
So there's not a separation between those two.

233
00:09:48.960 --> 00:09:50.320
Who David is on the inside

234
00:09:50.320 --> 00:09:52.440
and who is coming out on the outside

235
00:09:52.440 --> 00:09:53.840
in his praise.

236
00:09:53.840 --> 00:09:55.960
So let's see the kind of external expressions

237
00:09:55.960 --> 00:09:57.600
of praise here.

238
00:09:57.600 --> 00:09:58.800
You've got thanksgiving.

239
00:09:58.800 --> 00:10:00.800
Says I will give thanks.

240
00:10:00.800 --> 00:10:03.360
So David here is recognizing the grace of God

241
00:10:03.360 --> 00:10:05.960
and the good gifts that he has received from him

242
00:10:05.960 --> 00:10:07.720
and he's offering them back up to the Lord

243
00:10:07.720 --> 00:10:10.480
in his praise of thanksgiving.

244
00:10:11.440 --> 00:10:12.960
So that's the appropriate response

245
00:10:12.960 --> 00:10:15.320
to receiving a gift to say thank you

246
00:10:15.320 --> 00:10:17.000
to express gratitude.

247
00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:18.520
And certainly as the people of God now,

248
00:10:18.520 --> 00:10:19.720
people who are in Christ,

249
00:10:19.720 --> 00:10:22.360
we're called to as Colossians chapter two,

250
00:10:22.360 --> 00:10:23.240
verse seven says,

251
00:10:23.240 --> 00:10:26.360
we're called to be abounding in thanksgiving.

252
00:10:26.360 --> 00:10:27.960
Another verse from Colossians,

253
00:10:27.960 --> 00:10:30.640
it says, whatever you do in word or deed,

254
00:10:30.640 --> 00:10:33.600
do everything in the name of the Lord Jesus,

255
00:10:33.600 --> 00:10:36.960
giving thanks to God the Father through him.

256
00:10:36.960 --> 00:10:39.240
So if we're receiving all of life

257
00:10:39.240 --> 00:10:42.840
and all of God's good gifts in Christ,

258
00:10:42.840 --> 00:10:45.880
we're then to pass that back in praise

259
00:10:45.880 --> 00:10:47.120
and thanksgiving to him.

260
00:10:47.120 --> 00:10:48.840
All right, so thanksgiving.

261
00:10:48.840 --> 00:10:52.520
Also another external expression is recounting.

262
00:10:52.520 --> 00:10:57.520
Jesus says I will recount all of your wonderful deeds.

263
00:10:57.640 --> 00:11:00.680
What this is is this is remembering specific things

264
00:11:00.680 --> 00:11:03.800
that the Lord has done and speaking them out.

265
00:11:03.800 --> 00:11:07.320
So remembering, recounting and telling them out.

266
00:11:08.200 --> 00:11:10.120
So how might we do this?

267
00:11:10.120 --> 00:11:11.200
Well, when you read his word

268
00:11:11.200 --> 00:11:13.320
and you see all the things that the Lord has done,

269
00:11:13.320 --> 00:11:16.180
we can praise him for those things.

270
00:11:17.180 --> 00:11:18.940
When you walk with the Lord through the years,

271
00:11:18.940 --> 00:11:21.060
you can look back over your life

272
00:11:21.060 --> 00:11:23.700
