00:13:58.940 --> 00:14:01.420
I mentioned this a moment ago, but Colossians 3.16.

335
00:14:01.420 --> 00:14:03.500
Let the word of Christ dwell in you richly,

336
00:14:03.500 --> 00:14:06.700
teaching and admonishing one another in all wisdom,

337
00:14:06.700 --> 00:14:09.780
singing psalms and hymns and spiritual songs

338
00:14:09.780 --> 00:14:13.780
with thankfulness in your hearts to God.

339
00:14:13.780 --> 00:14:15.140
So we were just doing that a moment ago,

340
00:14:15.140 --> 00:14:16.820
singing praises to God.

341
00:14:18.020 --> 00:14:20.500
And later on in the service, we do this from time to time.

342
00:14:20.500 --> 00:14:22.300
We may have done it a couple of times before,

343
00:14:22.300 --> 00:14:24.860
but we're gonna have a time of just to follow exactly

344
00:14:24.860 --> 00:14:26.140
what we're being told to do here.

345
00:14:26.140 --> 00:14:27.940
What we might call declarative praise,

346
00:14:27.940 --> 00:14:32.140
where we are speaking out the promises of God's word

347
00:14:32.140 --> 00:14:33.940
over one another, just kind of thinking,

348
00:14:33.940 --> 00:14:36.060
okay, this is something the Lord has really spoken to me

349
00:14:36.060 --> 00:14:37.540
about in his word recently.

350
00:14:37.580 --> 00:14:41.060
I'm gonna read out that particular verse or whatever it is.

351
00:14:41.060 --> 00:14:42.340
But also prayers of thanksgiving.

352
00:14:42.340 --> 00:14:45.180
We'll have an open time where folks can just stand

