354
00:14:47.580 --> 00:14:49.220
So just to prime the pump for that,

355
00:14:49.220 --> 00:14:50.260
that's coming a bit later on,

356
00:14:50.260 --> 00:14:52.820
so we're gonna practice what's actually in here.

357
00:14:53.820 --> 00:14:54.740
But here I want us to see this.

358
00:14:54.740 --> 00:14:58.940
Praise isn't just an external expression.

359
00:14:58.940 --> 00:15:01.980
It's this external expression that is springing

360
00:15:01.980 --> 00:15:04.220
from an internal devotion.

361
00:15:04.220 --> 00:15:06.940
So praise isn't just about our songs and our thanksgiving

362
00:15:07.300 --> 00:15:08.820
and that kind of thing.

363
00:15:08.820 --> 00:15:11.460
It's being submitted to the Lord on the inside

364
00:15:11.460 --> 00:15:13.460
and being aware of his grace

365
00:15:13.460 --> 00:15:15.900
and all that he has given to us.

366
00:15:15.900 --> 00:15:17.300
So it's internal devotion.

367
00:15:18.380 --> 00:15:22.620
I think we all know it's possible to sing songs on Sunday

368
00:15:22.620 --> 00:15:25.580
or to say the right things when around certain people,

369
00:15:25.580 --> 00:15:28.420
when your heart is actually away from the Lord,

370
00:15:28.420 --> 00:15:30.700
you're not really thinking about him,

371
00:15:30.700 --> 00:15:33.740
but you kind of know how to keep up the facade.

372
00:15:34.740 --> 00:15:38.020
And Jesus quoted a verse in Isaiah 29

373
00:15:38.020 --> 00:15:42.220
