00:17:39.260 --> 00:17:40.580
Like if you went to a concert,

409
00:17:40.580 --> 00:17:42.100
you really enjoyed this past weekend.

410
00:17:42.100 --> 00:17:44.580
Like you'd be talking about it this morning,

411
00:17:44.580 --> 00:17:47.700
you know, or a game or a festival, whatever.

412
00:17:47.700 --> 00:17:50.760
You get help talk about what you enjoy.

413
00:17:51.680 --> 00:17:55.400
So true praise flows from hearts

414
00:17:55.400 --> 00:18:00.400
that are delighting in God and rejoicing in him above all else.

415
00:18:02.160 --> 00:18:06.240
You know, in exalting carries the idea of rejoicing in triumph.

416
00:18:06.240 --> 00:18:09.320
Our English word exalts comes from an old Latin word,

