00:34:12.840 --> 00:34:14.880
for everything that we have.

792
00:34:14.880 --> 00:34:17.560
And if we were, if we humbled ourselves

793
00:34:19.040 --> 00:34:20.680
beneath this highly exalted God

794
00:34:20.680 --> 00:34:23.880
that we would be depending on him,

795
00:34:23.880 --> 00:34:27.080
and that would then in turn fuel our praise

796
00:34:27.080 --> 00:34:28.440
because if we're depending on him,

797
00:34:28.440 --> 00:34:30.480
praying for him about everything,

798
00:34:30.480 --> 00:34:31.880
then we see, well actually,

799
00:34:31.880 --> 00:34:34.440
Lord, you answered this prayer and that prayer

800
00:34:34.440 --> 00:34:36.120
and this one I'm gonna recount

801
00:34:36.120 --> 00:34:38.840
all of your wonderful deeds today.

802
00:34:38.840 --> 00:34:40.040
Right, so that humble dependency

803
00:34:40.120 --> 00:34:45.040
leads to joyful prayer and praise.

804
00:34:45.240 --> 00:34:48.000
So we pray as people of need

805
00:34:48.000 --> 00:34:52.120
and then we praise him as recipients of his grace

806
00:34:52.120 --> 00:34:54.760
even when things are hard.

807
00:34:54.760 --> 00:34:56.160
You know, and sometimes our praise

808
00:34:56.160 --> 00:35:00.720
needs to defy the appearance of our circumstances.

809
00:35:00.720 --> 00:35:02.880
Could you turn with me to Hebrews chapter 13?

